<b>Subject:</b> Re: 20dmg 40dly?? what kind is this?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2065" TARGET=_self>20dmg 40dly?? what kind is this?</A> (Stridar)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> Just wondering where you heard of this bow. I am a fletcher with

<BR>&gt; 190 skill. Best I have made is 21 dmg 65 dly, a oak bow. I know
<BR>&gt; dark wood will do more dmg but also will have higher dly. Even
<BR>&gt; with all the gizmos added it does not have this dmg and dly. So
<BR>&gt; exacly what bow are you referrig to?
<P>A Runed Oak Bow:
<P>Damage: 21
<BR>Atkspd: 43
<BR>Range: 100
<P>Where to find: Dunno.
<P>None the less, even the bow you make is wicked. 21 dmg is significant. Surely it is better than sitting rooted to a spot while your foe blasts you to nothing. To be honest, I have never used a bow, but as a Wizard, I am sure that getting hit by one while trying to kill you would suck alot more than you just standing there rooted doing nothing at all.
<P>For sure, though, warriors need some sort of auto attack that works...Shadow Step is virtually useless agaisnt NPC Monsters as they find you almost immediately, while a PC has to spin around in circles trying to relocate his victim. Also....Woe to the warrior with 31k connections chasing a broadband wizzy around....will not work. BUT an auto attack/chase funtion will do the trick.
<P>-Gray
<P>PS Would you please go to our web site...then to our message board links...then to the market place adn advertise the sale of your bows? I know several of our guild that would be interested if you do in fact sell them. Thanks.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
